  "doc_id": "30522",
  "text": "SMCHD1 is a good candidate for a role in epigenetic modification. The gene was initially identified as a modifier of transgene variegation in mice [CITATION_1] and has since been shown to be required for a number of epigenetic processes including establishment and maintenance of CpG methylation on the inactive X chromosome (50-53), mono-allelic expression repression of imprinted genes and repression of repetitive sequences [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Recently, SMCHD1 was shown also to play a role in DNA repair of doublestrand breaks [CITATION_4] .",
